              <p>The cost to repair an induction cooktop can vary significantly depending on the brand. Here’s a look at some popular brands and what you might expect in terms of repair costs:</p>

              <h3>Bosch</h3>
              <p>
                Bosch is known for its high-quality and reliable kitchen appliances, including induction cooktops. However, repairing a Bosch induction cooktop can be relatively expensive. The cost of replacement parts, such as a control board or a glass top, can range from <b>$150 to $400</b>. Labor costs for a certified Bosch technician usually add another <b>$100 to $200</b>, bringing the total repair cost to approximately <b>$250 to $600</b>. Bosch parts are generally available, but their premium quality often means a higher price.
              </p>

              <h3>GE (General Electric)</h3>
              <p>
                GE induction cooktops are widely used and are considered moderately priced in the market. Repair costs for GE models tend to be more affordable compared to some other high-end brands. Parts like induction coils or control panels often range from <b>$50 to $250</b>, depending on the specific model. Labor costs for GE repairs typically add <b>$80 to $150</b> to the total bill. Overall, you can expect to spend between <b>$130 and $400</b> for most common repairs on a GE induction cooktop.
              </p>

              <h3>Samsung</h3>
              <p>
                Samsung induction cooktops are known for their innovative features and stylish designs. The cost of repairing a Samsung cooktop can vary but is generally in the mid-range. Replacement parts such as temperature sensors or touchpads can cost between <b>$50 and $300</b>. Labor charges are usually around <b>$100 to $200</b>. Consequently, the total repair cost for a Samsung induction cooktop often falls between <b>$150 and $500</b>. Samsung's wide availability of parts can sometimes help in reducing repair times and costs.
              </p>

              <h3>Whirlpool</h3>
              <p>
                Whirlpool is a trusted brand in the home appliance industry, offering reliable induction cooktops at a reasonable price point. Repairing a Whirlpool induction cooktop is generally affordable, with parts like heating elements or power cords costing between <b>$30 and $200</b>. Labor costs for repairs typically range from <b>$70 to $150</b>. In total, you can expect to pay between <b>$100 and $350</b> for most Whirlpool induction cooktop repairs. The availability of parts and the brand’s extensive service network often contribute to quicker and more affordable repairs.
              </p>

              <h3>Thermador</h3>
              <p>
                Thermador is a luxury brand known for its high-end kitchen appliances, including induction cooktops. Repair costs for Thermador models are usually on the higher side due to the premium nature of the brand. Replacement parts like control boards or glass tops can range from <b>$200 to $500</b>. The labor costs for a certified Thermador technician typically add another<b> $150 to $250</b>. Therefore, the total repair cost for a Thermador induction cooktop can easily range from <b>$350 to $750</b>. The use of high-quality materials and advanced technology in Thermador appliances often justifies the higher repair costs.
              </p>

              <h3>Frigidaire</h3>
              <p>
                Frigidaire offers a range of affordable induction cooktops known for their reliability and ease of use. Repair costs for Frigidaire models are generally lower compared to premium brands. Replacement parts such as cooling fans or fuses typically cost between <b>$20 and $150</b>. Labor charges usually add <b>$60 to $120</b> to the total repair bill. Overall, you can expect to pay between <b>$80 and $270</b> for most common repairs on a Frigidaire induction cooktop. The affordability of both parts and labor makes Frigidaire a cost-effective option for repairs.
              </p>

              <p>
                In summary, the cost to repair an induction cooktop can vary widely depending on the brand, with luxury brands like Thermador commanding higher repair costs compared to more budget-friendly options like Frigidaire. Always consider both parts and labor costs, and consult with a certified technician for an accurate estimate tailored to your specific model.
