            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <b>Regular Cleaning</b>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <b>Daily Wipe Down:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>After each use, allow the cooktop to cool down completely.</li>
                    <li>Use a soft, damp cloth or sponge to wipe away any spills or splatters.</li>
                    <li>For tougher stains, use a specialized induction cooktop cleaner or a mild dish soap solution.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Avoid Abrasives:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Do not use abrasive sponges, steel wool, or harsh chemical cleaners as they can scratch the glass surface.</li>
                    <li>For stubborn stains, a plastic or silicone scraper can be used gently.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ol>
              <b>Deep Cleaning</b>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <b>Weekly Maintenance:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Once a week, give your cooktop a more thorough cleaning.</li>
                    <li>Apply a small amount of cooktop cleaner to the surface and spread it with a soft cloth.</li>
                    <li>Let it sit for a few minutes to break down any residue, then buff it out with a clean, dry cloth.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Cleaning Around the Edges:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Pay attention to the edges and corners where grime can accumulate.</li>
                    <li>Use a cotton swab or a soft brush dipped in a mild cleaning solution to clean these areas.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ol>
              <b>Component Care</b>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <b>Cooling Fans:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Ensure the cooling fans are not obstructed and are working efficiently.</li>
                    <li>Periodically check the vents for dust and debris. Use a soft brush or compressed air to clean them.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Induction Coils:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>While the induction coils themselves are not directly accessible, keeping the cooktop surface clean helps prevent any issues with the coils.</li>
                    <li>If you notice any irregular heating or noise, it might be a sign that the coils need professional inspection.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ol>
              <b>Proper Usage</b>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <b>Suitable Cookware:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Always use cookware that is compatible with induction cooktops. This includes pots and pans with a flat, magnetic bottom.</li>
                    <li>Avoid using damaged or warped cookware as it can affect heating efficiency and potentially damage the cooktop.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Avoid Overheating:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Be mindful of the power settings and avoid using the highest setting for extended periods unless necessary.</li>
                    <li>Use the appropriate heat level for the type of cooking you are doing to prevent unnecessary strain on the cooktop.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ol>
              <b>Professional Maintenance</b>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <b>Annual Check-Up:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Consider scheduling an annual professional maintenance check to ensure all components are functioning correctly.</li>
                    <li>Professional technicians can inspect and clean the internal parts, ensuring your cooktop remains in optimal condition.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Timely Repairs:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Address any issues or malfunctions promptly. Delaying repairs can lead to more significant problems and higher costs.</li>
                    <li>Choose a reputable service provider that offers warranties on their repairs for added peace of mind.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
